content.thinking:
The user is saying the anchor is messing up the zoom. Let me look at the anchor detection logic:

```javascript
// Check if we're near the right edge
const currentTime = Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000);
const allData = dataFeed.getAllData();
const latestDataTime = allData.length > 0 ? allData[allData.length - 1].time : currentTime;
// Improved detection: within 1 candle of the latest data
const isNearRightEdge = currentTo >= latestDataTime - (granularityToSeconds[currentGranularity] || 60);
```

The problem is that it's anchoring to the right edge whenever you're within 1 candle of the latest data. This is too aggressive and makes it hard to zoom out when viewing recent data.

I should change the behavior to:
1. Only anchor when explicitly requested (with Shift key)
2. Or make the detection much more strict - like only when viewing the exact current time
3. Or remove the automatic anchoring entirely and let users zoom freely

I think the best approach is to remove automatic anchoring and only anchor when the user holds Shift. This gives full control to the user.

